<br>
The log bug was fixed with this patch. I ask because if you didn't, and you cut the pre-patch stuff in half, the avvodiance looks similar.<br>
<br>
After doing some light blue soloing, and allso an EXP group in the CT Throne Room; I think we hon estly were nerfed a little too hard.  If VI wants to bring us down a rung fine, but right now it's seems that instead of one rung, they've thrown us to the bottom of the ladder.<br>
<br>
I honestly think they need to either increae our mitigation a bit (not to where it was before, but I'm taking about 30% more damage on fights, and I honestly think that's VERY harsh); OR up our innate avoidance at bit again, (I'm not saying to a level where we would negate the nerf they feel was necessary), but at least to a point where we don't go down in 5 hits even though you have 2K HP.<br>
<br>
I feel like a meleeing Druid atm.  If the changes remain as is, I too will be cancelling my EQ acount FOR GOOD, and WILL NEVER play anther VI/Sony produced product (even though I'm a big Sci Fi fan, I refuse to invest my time/energy into a antoer game game where, given company policy, the SAME 'retunuing' garbage will happen due the the Dev Team NOT UNDERSTANDING their own friggn' game -- yes, I believe you'll see stuff like this again when SWG is 3 years along).<br>
<br>
We didn't get hit with a Nerf stick, it was a Nerk Sledgehammer. <p><center><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30466" TARGET="_blank"><image src = "http://www.catplex.org/chilau/chilau_fk5.jpg"></a>
